<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<Weakness xmlns="http://cwe.mitre.org/cwe-7" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" ID="474" Name="Use of Function with Inconsistent Implementations" Abstraction="Base" Structure="Simple" Status="Draft">
         <Description>The code uses a function that has inconsistent implementations across operating systems and versions.</Description>
         <Extended_Description>
            <xhtml:p>The use of inconsistent implementations can cause changes in behavior when the code is ported or built under a different environment than the programmer expects, which can lead to security problems in some cases.</xhtml:p>
            <xhtml:p>The implementation of many functions varies by platform, and at times, even by different versions of the same platform. Implementation differences can include:</xhtml:p>
               <xhtml:ul>
                  <xhtml:li>Slight differences in the way parameters are interpreted leading to inconsistent results.</xhtml:li>
                  <xhtml:li>Some implementations of the function carry significant security risks.</xhtml:li>
                  <xhtml:li>The function might not be defined on all platforms.</xhtml:li>
                  <xhtml:li>The function might change which return codes it can provide, or change the meaning of its return codes.</xhtml:li>
               </xhtml:ul>
         </Extended_Description>
         <Related_Weaknesses>
            <Related_Weakness Nature="ChildOf" CWE_ID="758" View_ID="1000" Ordinal="Primary" />
         </Related_Weaknesses>
         <Weakness_Ordinalities>
            <Weakness_Ordinality>
